# SPEC — Deepsuck Harness

> The runtime container for Deepsuck Agent. Enforces DAG-first behavior via SOUL.md constitution. Bridge between spec graph and agent behavior.

---

## Product

The Deepsuck Harness loads the DAG-first constitution (SOUL.md), enforces truth hierarchy (DAG > SOUL > code > context), runs the compounding loop (compile → validate → score), and applies guardrails: self-audit trapdoor every 5 tool calls, confidence markers on every code answer, and 5 hard blocks that cannot be bypassed.

## What the User Sees

The user writes code and specs. The harness silently enforces:
- No code read before .dag load
- No spec edit without recompile + validate + score report
- No commit without validation pass
- No speculation about spec structure
- No silent code fixes that contradict spec

The agent self-audits every 5 tool calls. Answers carry [DAG: X/10] grounding scores. Score regressions are blocked.

## Flow: Agent Startup

```
[1] Load SOUL.md as system prompt prefix
[2] Load project .dag into context
[3] Print: "Loaded <project>.dag: N entities, M relationships, score X%"
[4] Agent is now grounded. May read code files.
```
